   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1385.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   No topic header</span><hr size=1> Yes, this is a private message board.  You are here at Jaxy's pleasure.  [bold] However [/bold] I would hope the goal of this (or any other message board) is to facilitate the free expression of ideas.  If it's not, what is the point of ever bothering to express yourself?   Why go through the effort to post here under the pretense of freedom of expression when you can see you really have none because of the moderation/ownership? <br>
<br>
My suggestion isn't that the moderators need to be replaced, it's that they need to do their job, without ado, without taunting, and without ego.  Unfortunately, we've already seen that must be incredibly tough for some of the mod's, because mostly they [bold] enjoy [/bold] banning people with whom they disagree.  To me, that isn't right.  Agree or disagree, respect or disrespect, and even love or hate, people should be treated as equitably as possible by the mod's.  That's their job.  They aren't doing it very well, but that doesn't mean that they can't.<br>
<br>
I don't own the board, I don't run the board, and I certainly don't moderate the board, but that doesn't mean that my opinions (or everyone else's opinions) have no bearing or weight.  I would hope that the owner of the board would be more interested in the liberty of the board users to say their opinions, than whether they agree with the opinion.<br>
<br>
Zel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujharycleric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jharycleric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/16/02 9:57:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1385.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No topic header</span><hr size=1> I can't make cookies for the moderators, but I have pie.<br>
<br>
And it's not new mods we need, it's new posters. Half the people on here couldn't think their way through a door, much less type out a thoughtful, coherent post.<br>
<br>
In response to Zel. That's all well and good, but what is a moderators job then? As near as I can see from what your posting, it's to........what? Stay out of the way? Add new posting areas? If it is not to do the job they are currently doing, then what would it be? Personally I think they let people get away with much more than I would. Reading the same exact posting rules they do, I would interpret them much harsher. They draw a more lenient line then I would, but I gather you would have them draw an even softer line on what's posted. At that point we are now arguing not the rule, but how we would want the rule interpretted. Just because we would interpret it differently does not mean that one is bad, or not doing the job right, but merely doing it differently than you or I. <br>
<br>
To me, most of the complaining falls into the &quot;Peach Pie is best&quot; area. It's not a fact, it's an opinon. Some people hate peach pie. Some think pumpkin is best. The people on SZ prefer Twinkies.<br>
<br>
Jhary<br>
